try to use a defense like this

00:25:07.710 --> 00:25:09.600 align:middle line:84%
because they think
they can escape.

00:25:09.600 --> 00:25:11.400 align:middle line:84%
They're overworked,
they're overburdened.

00:25:11.400 --> 00:25:13.066 align:middle line:84%
And I said, yeah,
that would pretty much

00:25:13.066 --> 00:25:14.010 align:middle line:90%
describe my attorney.

00:25:14.010 --> 00:25:15.370 align:middle line:90%
He said, yeah, I thought so.

00:25:15.370 --> 00:25:17.494 align:middle line:84%
He said, well that doesn't
mean it's going to work,

00:25:17.494 --> 00:25:18.400 align:middle line:90%
you understand.

00:25:18.400 --> 00:25:21.680 align:middle line:84%
And at that point, I
really expected to go home.

00:25:21.680 --> 00:25:26.860 align:middle line:84%
And I thought that my stupid
attorney had blown his strategy

00:25:26.860 --> 00:25:30.760 align:middle line:84%
and that I was going to have
to serve this prison time,

00:25:30.760 --> 00:25:34.070 align:middle line:84%
get out of jail, and go
right back to square one

00:25:34.070 --> 00:25:37.890 align:middle line:84%
and start all over again and try
to find some money to-- raise

00:25:37.890 --> 00:25:40.500 align:middle line:84%
some private funding to
hire a private attorney.

00:25:40.500 --> 00:25:44.010 align:middle line:84%
And that's what
should have happened.

00:25:44.010 --> 00:25:48.440 align:middle line:84%
But, of course, my case
was loaded with politics.

00:25:48.440 --> 00:25:53.610 align:middle line:84%
And by this time, we were losing
the war in Iraq really badly.

00:25:53.610 --> 00:25:56.210 align:middle line:84%
Americans-- I mean, I
have to stop and say

00:25:56.210 --> 00:25:59.100 align:middle line:84%
that American soldiers
and the Iraqi people

00:25:59.100 --> 00:26:01.720 align:middle line:84%
were the greatest
victims of all.

00:26:01.720 --> 00:26:05.480 align:middle line:84%
And what I was suffering
at the start of this,

00:26:05.480 --> 00:26:09.340 align:middle line:84%
J-- I had a wonderful
companion named JB Fields, who

00:26:09.340 --> 00:26:12.309 align:middle line:84%
was himself retired
military, and he

00:26:12.309 --> 00:26:14.600 align:middle line:84%
used to say, Susan, if you
think what you are suffering

00:26:14.600 --> 00:26:16.941 align:middle line:84%
is bad-- right up
until I go to prison.

00:26:16.941 --> 00:26:18.190 align:middle line:90%
Right up until I go to prison.

00:26:18.190 --> 00:26:20.670 align:middle line:84%
When I was free
on bail, he said,

00:26:20.670 --> 00:26:22.050 align:middle line:84%
"Susan, if you
think this is bad,

00:26:22.050 --> 00:26:24.510 align:middle line:84%
just think what the American
soldiers are suffering.

00:26:24.510 --> 00:26:26.500 align:middle line:84%
Somebody's going to
lose his leg tonight.

00:26:26.500 --> 00:26:28.660 align:middle line:84%
Somebody's going to be
paralyzed tomorrow morning."

00:26:28.660 --> 00:26:29.400 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Someone's
going to be killed.

00:26:29.400 --> 00:26:31.108 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: Someone's
going to be killed,

00:26:31.108 --> 00:26:32.400 align:middle line:90%
and they did not deserve this.

00:26:32.400 --> 00:26:34.340 align:middle line:90%
They didn't get into this war.

00:26:34.340 --> 00:26:35.820 align:middle line:84%
They're the ones
who are suffering

00:26:35.820 --> 00:26:37.410 align:middle line:90%
the most from these lies.

00:26:37.410 --> 00:26:40.690 align:middle line:84%
He said, "Think about the
Iraqi people whose houses

00:26:40.690 --> 00:26:43.730 align:middle line:84%
are destroyed, whose schools
are destroyed, who've lost

00:26:43.730 --> 00:26:45.260 align:middle line:90%
control of their country."

00:26:45.260 --> 00:26:49.030 align:middle line:84%
He said, "Anything that you
feel that makes you feel angry,"

00:26:49.030 --> 00:26:51.320 align:middle line:84%
he said, "don't feel
sorry for yourself."

00:26:51.320 --> 00:26:52.190 align:middle line:90%
I loved him.

00:26:52.190 --> 00:26:55.320 align:middle line:90%
He died-- he died of cancer.

00:26:55.320 --> 00:26:58.500 align:middle line:84%
But he refused to allow
me to feel self-pity.

00:26:58.500 --> 00:27:00.740 align:middle line:84%
Because he said, you need
to stand by your values.

00:27:00.740 --> 00:27:03.610 align:middle line:84%
He challenged me to
stand by my values

00:27:03.610 --> 00:27:05.370 align:middle line:90%
and to take responsibility.

00:27:05.370 --> 00:27:08.410 align:middle line:90%
And I chose this.

00:27:08.410 --> 00:27:09.940 align:middle line:90%
I absolutely did.

00:27:09.940 --> 00:27:12.260 align:middle line:84%
And to be perfectly honest
with you, the reason I still

00:27:12.260 --> 00:27:14.170 align:middle line:84%
have a smile on
my face at all is

00:27:14.170 --> 00:27:16.630 align:middle line:84%
because I believe I
did the right thing.

00:27:16.630 --> 00:27:19.780 align:middle line:84%
I was ready to take any
consequences I had to take,

00:27:19.780 --> 00:27:22.840 align:middle line:84%
but I never backed
down for a minute.

00:27:22.840 --> 00:27:25.580 align:middle line:84%
And I always stood up
for what I believed in.

00:27:25.580 --> 00:27:30.230 align:middle line:84%
But when I got into Carswell,
that's when it got scary

00:27:30.230 --> 00:27:34.440 align:middle line:84%
and they began to rewrite
the history of my life.

00:27:34.440 --> 00:27:38.070 align:middle line:84%
They began to say that
I was quote, delusional.

00:27:38.070 --> 00:27:41.500 align:middle line:84%
That I was suffering from
grandiosity and severe

00:27:41.500 --> 00:27:42.960 align:middle line:90%
paranoia.

00:27:42.960 --> 00:27:44.660 align:middle line:84%
I was like, well,
this is ridiculous.

00:27:44.660 --> 00:27:47.820 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: This was Dr.
Voss and Dr. Peterson?

00:27:47.820 --> 00:27:50.140 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: Peterson,
Dr. Peterson of Carswell.

00:27:50.140 --> 00:27:50.820 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:27:50.820 --> 00:27:54.290 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: And
they freely admitted

00:27:54.290 --> 00:27:56.860 align:middle line:84%
that they never saw any
evidence of schizophrenia

00:27:56.860 --> 00:28:00.960 align:middle line:84%
or hallucinations or hearing
voices, or any depression.

00:28:00.960 --> 00:28:07.670 align:middle line:84%
But I became terrorized because
even though they admitted

00:28:07.670 --> 00:28:09.870 align:middle line:84%
there were no
psychiatric symptoms--

00:28:09.870 --> 00:28:15.120 align:middle line:84%
and they freely said that--
they refused to release me

00:28:15.120 --> 00:28:18.190 align:middle line:84%
from prison, and they filed
the papers with the court

00:28:18.190 --> 00:28:20.732 align:middle line:84%
that I should be
detained indefinitely.

00:28:20.732 --> 00:28:21.940 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Now, first of all--

00:28:21.940 --> 00:28:23.500 align:middle line:90%
>>LINDAUER: Up to 10 years.

00:28:23.500 --> 00:28:24.958 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And
normally when someone

00:28:24.958 --> 00:28:28.320 align:middle line:84%
