evaluation, into this prison,

00:28:28.320 --> 00:28:29.530 align:middle line:90%
it's 120 days.

00:28:29.530 --> 00:28:31.585 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It's
actually six weeks.

00:28:31.585 --> 00:28:32.585 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Six weeks, OK.

00:28:32.585 --> 00:28:33.876 align:middle line:90%
>>LINDAUER: Six to eight weeks.

00:28:33.876 --> 00:28:35.980 align:middle line:84%
And the only reason
it takes that long

00:28:35.980 --> 00:28:37.840 align:middle line:84%
is because they've
got so many inmates,

00:28:37.840 --> 00:28:40.960 align:middle line:84%
and they're processing them
as rapidly as they can,

00:28:40.960 --> 00:28:43.050 align:middle line:90%
but they have to study people.

00:28:43.050 --> 00:28:45.850 align:middle line:84%
People who were
there for 120 days

00:28:45.850 --> 00:28:49.070 align:middle line:84%
are usually detox
cases, where they've

00:28:49.070 --> 00:28:52.420 align:middle line:84%
been on some sort of
psychiatric drug or heroin

00:28:52.420 --> 00:28:53.564 align:middle line:90%
or some kind of morphine.

00:28:53.564 --> 00:28:55.730 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And you didn't
qualify under that category

00:28:55.730 --> 00:28:57.510 align:middle line:84%
because you're very much
against drug taking.

00:28:57.510 --> 00:28:58.520 align:middle line:90%
>>LINDAUER: Absolutely.

00:28:58.520 --> 00:29:01.470 align:middle line:84%
So I had-- but they
have to detox somebody

00:29:01.470 --> 00:29:03.830 align:middle line:84%
before they can find out
what they really are like,

00:29:03.830 --> 00:29:06.970 align:middle line:84%
and whether they really are
incompetent to stand trial.

00:29:06.970 --> 00:29:11.496 align:middle line:84%
And so that's the only time that
you keep someone from 120 days.

00:29:11.496 --> 00:29:13.370 align:middle line:84%
Otherwise, you send them
right back to court.

00:29:13.370 --> 00:29:15.510 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But they're going
to keep you up to 10 years.

00:29:15.510 --> 00:29:17.280 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: But they
demanded the right

00:29:17.280 --> 00:29:20.010 align:middle line:84%
to detain me indefinitely
up to 10 years.

00:29:20.010 --> 00:29:21.950 align:middle line:84%
They told the court
that my belief

00:29:21.950 --> 00:29:26.120 align:middle line:84%
in my experiences as an asset
were so deeply ingrained.

00:29:26.120 --> 00:29:28.712 align:middle line:90%


00:29:28.712 --> 00:29:30.420 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: In your
memory and imagination.

00:29:30.420 --> 00:29:32.670 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: My
memory was so strong

00:29:32.670 --> 00:29:39.180 align:middle line:84%
that it would require extra
hard work to break my spirit

00:29:39.180 --> 00:29:42.340 align:middle line:84%
and to break me of my
belief in my identity.

00:29:42.340 --> 00:29:47.207 align:middle line:84%
And that it would take
several years, up to 10 years,

00:29:47.207 --> 00:29:49.040 align:middle line:84%
and that they would be
sure to let the court

00:29:49.040 --> 00:29:52.640 align:middle line:84%
know when I had been convinced
that I no longer believed

00:29:52.640 --> 00:29:55.190 align:middle line:84%
that I had warned about
9/11, and I no longer

00:29:55.190 --> 00:29:56.890 align:middle line:84%
believed in the Iraqi
peace option, or--

00:29:56.890 --> 00:29:58.350 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And that you no longer
believed you were an asset.

00:29:58.350 --> 00:29:59.891 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: --that
I'd been an asset.

00:29:59.891 --> 00:30:02.560 align:middle line:84%
Or that Richard Fuisz
or Paul Hoven existed.

00:30:02.560 --> 00:30:05.750 align:middle line:84%
At one point, it was so
crazy that they actually

00:30:05.750 --> 00:30:08.620 align:middle line:84%
said that Richard Fuisz might
be a figment of my imagination.

00:30:08.620 --> 00:30:13.150 align:middle line:84%
And I said, you are
psychotic if you think that.

00:30:13.150 --> 00:30:15.290 align:middle line:84%
And they're like--
and they kind of

00:30:15.290 --> 00:30:19.120 align:middle line:84%
tested me to see if I would back
down, and they were like, well,

00:30:19.120 --> 00:30:20.580 align:middle line:90%
but can you prove they exist?

00:30:20.580 --> 00:30:22.926 align:middle line:90%
I was like, yes, I can.

00:30:22.926 --> 00:30:27.460 align:middle line:84%
Can you prove Richard Fuisz
was a CIA asset, handler, a CIA

00:30:27.460 --> 00:30:28.220 align:middle line:90%
operative?

00:30:28.220 --> 00:30:31.880 align:middle line:84%
Yes, absolutely, because
the Justice Department

00:30:31.880 --> 00:30:36.380 align:middle line:84%
had issued a finding of
his intelligence status

00:30:36.380 --> 00:30:39.090 align:middle line:90%
in another case.

00:30:39.090 --> 00:30:42.350 align:middle line:84%
And so the Justice
Department had laid out

00:30:42.350 --> 00:30:45.630 align:middle line:84%
papers for a different
judge declaring

00:30:45.630 --> 00:30:47.120 align:middle line:90%
that Richard Fuisz was a major--

00:30:47.120 --> 00:30:47.911 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, yeah.

00:30:47.911 --> 00:30:50.510 align:middle line:84%
The point is all the evidence
was there that you were clear

00:30:50.510 --> 00:30:52.310 align:middle line:84%
on this, that all
the people existed,

00:30:52.310 --> 00:30:55.219 align:middle line:84%
you said-- They weren't going
to take that for an answer,

00:30:55.219 --> 00:30:57.510 align:middle line:84%
and they were going to see
that you were hung out there

00:30:57.510 --> 00:31:01.630 align:middle line:84%
in the middle of Texas
inside of a military base,

00:31:01.630 --> 00:31:03.399 align:middle line:84%
sight unseen for as
long as possible.

00:31:03.399 --> 00:31:05.440 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: Sight unseen
for as long as possible.

00:31:05.440 --> 00:31:07.023 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: OK, so now
then they started

00:31:07.023 --> 00:31:10.900 align:middle line:10%
pushing for drugging you
to help you be released

00:31:10.900 --> 00:31:15.264 align:middle line:10%
of these delusions, that you
are Susan Lindauer, a CIA asset.

00:31:15.264 --> 00:31:15.930 align:middle line:90%
>>LINDAUER: Yes.

00:31:15.930 --> 00:31:19.360 align:middle line:10%
What they said was that
treatment-- it was not

00:31:19.360 --> 00:31:22.010 align:middle line:10%
enough to just
detain me, they had

00:31:22.010 --> 00:31:24.930 align:middle line:10%
to chemically lobotomize me.

00:31:24.930 --> 00:31:28.550 align:middle line:10%
And I had seen them do this
to other women at Carswell.

00:31:28.550 --> 00:31:31.630 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: And I want you to talk
about this and share with us

00:31:31.630 --> 00:31:33.780 align:middle line:10%
now this portion of it.

00:31:33.780 --> 00:31:39.730 align:middle line:84%
You had first-hand witness
to just horrific effects

00:31:39.730 --> 00:31:42.009 align:middle line:84%
of these drugs, what it
did to these women's lives,

00:31:42.009 --> 00:31:43.800 align:middle line:84%
and I want you to tell
a few of those tales

00:31:43.800 --> 00:31:48.260 align:middle line:84%
before we get back into the fact
you fought like crazy to not

00:31:48.260 --> 00:31:49.300 align:middle line:90%
have that done to you.

00:31:49.300 --> 00:31:50.758 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: From
the very beginning

00:31:50.758 --> 00:31:54.370 align:middle line:84%
when I arrived at Carswell, I
saw that Carswell was overly

00:31:54.370 --> 00:31:57.580 align:middle line:84%
drugging inmates who
were very healthy.

00:31:57.580 --> 00:31:59.910 align:middle line:84%
I watched these women
arrive at the prison.

00:31:59.910 --> 00:32:05.200 align:middle line:84%
They were friendly, cooperative,
good communication skills.

00:32:05.200 --> 00:32:08.420 align:middle line:84%
The women on the
psych unit of Carswell

00:32:08.420 --> 00:32:09.630 align:middle line:90%
had something in common.

00:32:09.630 --> 00:32:11.109 align:middle line:90%
They were all middle class.

00:32:11.109 --> 00:32:13.650 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, I know people
will be surprised to hear that.

00:32:13.650 --> 00:32:15.800 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: They were
not violent offenders.

00:32:15.800 --> 00:32:17.300 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: How did
they end up there?

00:32:17.300 --> 00:32:19.591 align:middle line:84%
I mean, how did these middle
class people end up there?

00:32:19.591 --> 00:32:21.990 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: Most of
the women at Carswell

00:32:21.990 --> 00:32:24.820 align:middle line:90%
were passive followers.

00:32:24.820 --> 00:32:28.020 align:middle line:84%
Their husbands and
boyfriends had typically

00:32:28.020 --> 00:32:30.200 align:middle line:90%
done some real crime.

00:32:30.200 --> 00:32:32.660 align:middle line:84%
The husband or boyfriend
tried to kill somebody.

00:32:32.660 --> 00:32:34.596 align:middle line:84%
The husband or boyfriend
was a bank robber.

00:32:34.596 --> 00:32:35.720 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Or running drugs.

00:32:35.720 --> 00:32:36.928 align:middle line:90%
>>LINDAUER: Or running drugs.

00:32:36.928 --> 00:32:40.630 align:middle line:84%
Most of them were very
simply drug cases.

00:32:40.630 --> 00:32:45.000 align:middle line:84%
And the women were
very passive followers,

00:32:45.000 --> 00:32:50.300 align:middle line:84%
like they refused to testify
against their boyfriend,

00:32:50.300 --> 00:32:52.600 align:middle line:84%
or they lied, they
outright lied and tried

00:32:52.600 --> 00:32:56.740 align:middle line:84%
to create an alibi for them
called obstruction of justice.

00:32:56.740 --> 00:33:02.820 align:middle line:84%
So one of the women at Carswell
was given a 26 year term.

00:33:02.820 --> 00:33:05.470 align:middle line:90%
She was a great-grandmother.

00:33:05.470 --> 00:33:08.600 align:middle line:90%
And she was a black woman.

00:33:08.600 --> 00:33:11.970 align:middle line:84%
A lot of these are black
people, you have to understand,

00:33:11.970 --> 00:33:13.290 align:middle line:90%
they're black people.

00:33:13.290 --> 00:33:17.220 align:middle line:84%
And a black
great-grandmother whose

00:33:17.220 --> 00:33:21.530 align:middle line:84%
granddaughter was
involved in drugs.

00:33:21.530 --> 00:33:24.990 align:middle line:84%
And the great-grandmother
was taking care of the baby,

00:33:24.990 --> 00:33:27.870 align:middle line:84%
and she said she
could not testify

00:33:27.870 --> 00:33:30.310 align:middle line:84%
against her granddaughter
because it would cause

00:33:30.310 --> 00:33:31.710 align:middle line:84%
too many problems,
and she needed

00:33:31.710 --> 00:33:34.250 align:middle line:84%
to be there for that
child, who would otherwise

00:33:34.250 --> 00:33:37.900 align:middle line:84%
go into the foster care
system and be destroyed.

00:33:37.900 --> 00:33:39.560 align:middle line:84%
So the judge in her
case said, well,

00:33:39.560 --> 00:33:41.645 align:middle line:84%
since you won't
help society, I'm

00:33:41.645 --> 00:33:43.020 align:middle line:84%
going to make sure
that you never

00:33:43.020 --> 00:33:45.370 align:middle line:84%
see your
great-granddaughter again.

00:33:45.370 --> 00:33:48.100 align:middle line:84%
And so she gave her
a 26 year sentence.

00:33:48.100 --> 00:33:49.760 align:middle line:90%
The woman was a teetotaler.

00:33:49.760 --> 00:33:53.780 align:middle line:84%
Had never used
drugs in her life.

00:33:53.780 --> 00:33:59.100 align:middle line:84%
Another woman who I knew, who
was on the psych unit with me,

00:33:59.100 --> 00:34:02.090 align:middle line:84%
her boyfriend was
dealing in drugs,

00:34:02.090 --> 00:34:04.960 align:middle line:84%
moving drugs from
Chicago to Washington.

00:34:04.960 --> 00:34:08.099 align:middle line:84%
And she was, herself,
a piano teacher.

00:34:08.099 --> 00:34:11.380 align:middle line:84%
Now, again, she never
used drugs at all.

00:34:11.380 --> 00:34:16.520 align:middle line:84%
But they tried to say she-- they
did declare her incompetent,

00:34:16.520 --> 00:34:18.139 align:middle line:90%
and she was a piano teacher.

00:34:18.139 --> 00:34:21.955 align:middle line:84%
They asked her what type
of music she taught.

00:34:21.955 --> 00:34:23.580 align:middle line:84%
And she said, well,
I teach everything.

00:34:23.580 --> 00:34:24.880 align:middle line:90%
I teach jazz, R&B.

00:34:24.880 --> 00:34:27.020 align:middle line:84%
They're like, oh,
that's black music.

00:34:27.020 --> 00:34:28.929 align:middle line:90%
You can teach black music.

00:34:28.929 --> 00:34:31.880 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, well I graduated
from Howard University.

00:34:31.880 --> 00:34:36.139 align:middle line:84%
I'm a concert pianist level,
and I play Chopin and Mozart

00:34:36.139 --> 00:34:37.580 align:middle line:90%
as well.

00:34:37.580 --> 00:34:41.060 align:middle line:84%
Oh, well, now that's
another matter.

00:34:41.060 --> 00:34:44.880 align:middle line:84%
A black woman is not supposed
to play Chopin and Mozart.

00:34:44.880 --> 00:34:47.780 align:middle line:84%
They actually challenged
her competency.

00:34:47.780 --> 00:34:49.337 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Because she believed.

00:34:49.337 --> 00:34:51.170 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: They said
that she had delusions

00:34:51.170 --> 00:34:52.977 align:middle line:90%
of being in the middle class.

00:34:52.977 --> 00:34:53.560 align:middle line:90%
And the idea--

00:34:53.560 --> 00:34:55.310 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And a classical
concert pianist.

00:34:55.310 --> 00:34:59.660 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: That a black woman
would teach Chopin and Mozart.

00:34:59.660 --> 00:35:03.561 align:middle line:84%
The other was just the idea
that she could interpret it.

00:35:03.561 --> 00:35:05.810 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But you've got to
remember, you're in Texas.

00:35:05.810 --> 00:35:07.226 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: Yeah,
you're in Texas.

00:35:07.226 --> 00:35:09.380 align:middle line:84%
But the idea that you
could interpret it,

00:35:09.380 --> 00:35:12.140 align:middle line:84%
that you would understand it,
that you could appreciate it.

00:35:12.140 --> 00:35:17.030 align:middle line:84%
And also, the sickening part was
that she taught white children.

00:35:17.030 --> 00:35:19.710 align:middle line:84%
And they were like, you
think you're good enough

00:35:19.710 --> 00:35:23.540 align:middle line:84%
to teach a white child, a
white seven-year-old how

00:35:23.540 --> 00:35:24.760 align:middle line:90%
to play Mozart?

00:35:24.760 --> 00:35:26.840 align:middle line:90%
You think that you're qualified?

00:35:26.840 --> 00:35:28.570 align:middle line:84%
And so they declared
her--I mean,

00:35:28.570 --> 00:35:31.890 align:middle line:84%
can you imagine the destruction
of this woman's psyche

00:35:31.890 --> 00:35:34.700 align:middle line:84%
as they're saying, you know,
you think you're good enough

00:35:34.700 --> 00:35:36.980 align:middle line:90%
to teach our children?

00:35:36.980 --> 00:35:40.520 align:middle line:84%
And you don't teach-- and then
the third strike against her,

00:35:40.520 --> 00:35:42.800 align:middle line:84%
which by this time
was just, I was just--

00:35:42.800 --> 00:35:47.310 align:middle line:84%
I remember listening to this,
horrified just beyond, like,

00:35:47.310 --> 00:35:50.900 align:middle line:84%
oh my god, they didn't-- oh no,
that she taught white children

00:35:50.900 --> 00:35:52.560 align:middle line:90%
in her own home.

00:35:52.560 --> 00:35:55.060 align:middle line:84%
Because we all know that black
people can be servants and go

00:35:55.060 --> 00:35:57.600 align:middle line:84%
to a white household
as a servant,

00:35:57.600 --> 00:36:00.940 align:middle line:84%
but to expect a white child
to come into your neighborhood

00:36:00.940 --> 00:36:02.650 align:middle line:84%
and to sit down
at your piano, you

00:36:02.650 --> 00:36:06.010 align:middle line:84%
think your piano has enough
tuning for a white child?

00:36:06.010 --> 00:36:07.770 align:middle line:84%
This is what we were
dealing with here.

00:36:07.770 --> 00:36:09.640 align:middle line:90%
These people are nuts.

00:36:09.640 --> 00:36:11.250 align:middle line:90%
They are dangerous.

00:36:11.250 --> 00:36:11.750 align:middle line:90%
I mean--

00:36:11.750 --> 00:36:12.100 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Neanderthals, really.

00:36:12.100 --> 00:36:13.433 align:middle line:90%
>>LINDAUER: --the psychiatrists.

00:36:13.433 --> 00:36:16.200 align:middle line:84%
But this was a real case,
this was a real woman,

00:36:16.200 --> 00:36:18.470 align:middle line:84%
and she was declared
incompetent.

00:36:18.470 --> 00:36:19.800 align:middle line:90%
She was declared incompetent.

00:36:19.800 --> 00:36:21.980 align:middle line:84%
And she was, let
me just add, she

00:36:21.980 --> 00:36:25.780 align:middle line:84%
was a strong, confident,
motivated black woman

00:36:25.780 --> 00:36:26.770 align:middle line:90%
with attitude.

00:36:26.770 --> 00:36:28.690 align:middle line:90%
She did not swear or curse.

00:36:28.690 --> 00:36:30.500 align:middle line:84%
She was a middle
class black woman.

00:36:30.500 --> 00:36:32.110 align:middle line:90%
She was not ghetto.

00:36:32.110 --> 00:36:35.160 align:middle line:84%
But you see, if she
had been ghetto,

00:36:35.160 --> 00:36:37.295 align:middle line:84%
they would have said
well, you're black trash.

00:36:37.295 --> 00:36:38.100 align:middle line:90%
You're trash.

00:36:38.100 --> 00:36:39.720 align:middle line:84%
You're supposed to
be trash, and you

00:36:39.720 --> 00:36:42.011 align:middle line:84%
know you're supposed to be
trash and you're not uppity.

00:36:42.011 --> 00:36:46.590 align:middle line:84%
But the fact that she had
expectations of middle class

00:36:46.590 --> 00:36:48.940 align:middle line:84%
values and she thought
she was good enough

00:36:48.940 --> 00:36:51.160 align:middle line:84%
to be in the middle
class, oh my heavens.

00:36:51.160 --> 00:36:52.230 align:middle line:90%
I wept.

00:36:52.230 --> 00:36:54.620 align:middle line:84%
I was like-- but the
thing is, these people,

00:36:54.620 --> 00:36:57.800 align:middle line:90%
it was like-- it was terrifying.

00:36:57.800 --> 00:36:59.670 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I can tell
you these stories.

00:36:59.670 --> 00:37:03.870 align:middle line:84%
And another beautiful,
beautiful, young black woman,

00:37:03.870 --> 00:37:06.670 align:middle line:90%
a Spelman College student.

00:37:06.670 --> 00:37:11.530 align:middle line:84%
Spelman is a historically black
women's college in Atlanta,

00:37:11.530 --> 00:37:14.660 align:middle line:84%
and she'd been in the
top 10% of her class.

00:37:14.660 --> 00:37:17.200 align:middle line:84%
When she arrived, she was
like a sorority sister:

00:37:17.200 --> 00:37:22.430 align:middle line:84%
beautiful, exuberant,
confident, joyful.

00:37:22.430 --> 00:37:26.670 align:middle line:84%
And I remember the guards
said, she reads the newspaper.

00:37:26.670 --> 00:37:30.250 align:middle line:84%
A black woman who
reads the newspaper.

00:37:30.250 --> 00:37:34.660 align:middle line:84%
We were told never to
request a newspaper.

00:37:34.660 --> 00:37:35.770 align:middle line:90%
She did.

00:37:35.770 --> 00:37:36.770 align:middle line:90%
She made the mistake.

00:37:36.770 --> 00:37:39.860 align:middle line:84%
She was-- I guess she was
just doing what she does,

00:37:39.860 --> 00:37:43.260 align:middle line:84%
but the idea that a black
woman would be aware

00:37:43.260 --> 00:37:45.589 align:middle line:90%
of contemporary--

00:37:45.589 --> 00:37:46.630 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Current events.

00:37:46.630 --> 00:37:48.680 align:middle line:90%
>>LINDAUER: Current events.

00:37:48.680 --> 00:37:49.980 align:middle line:90%
She'd have ideas.

00:37:49.980 --> 00:37:53.180 align:middle line:90%
She'd be literate.

00:37:53.180 --> 00:37:54.940 align:middle line:84%
And this was not
a violent woman.

00:37:54.940 --> 00:37:56.856 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So this is
very frightening to them.

00:37:56.856 --> 00:37:59.348 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: Very, very, very
frightening to them and to us.

00:37:59.348 --> 00:38:01.181 align:middle line:84%
Because what they did
to this woman was they

00:38:01.181 --> 00:38:07.420 align:middle line:84%
demanded-- she was compliant,
and this was her mistake.

00:38:07.420 --> 00:38:10.810 align:middle line:84%
She had been taught to be a
good girl, to be obedient,

00:38:10.810 --> 00:38:13.300 align:middle line:84%
and if they told her to
do something, she did it.

00:38:13.300 --> 00:38:14.880 align:middle line:90%
So she agreed.

00:38:14.880 --> 00:38:18.510 align:middle line:84%
She allowed them to drug
her; she did not fight it.

00:38:18.510 --> 00:38:20.210 align:middle line:84%
And she agreed to
take whatever drugs

00:38:20.210 --> 00:38:24.170 align:middle line:84%
and they doped her
to the gills so

00:38:24.170 --> 00:38:27.160 align:middle line:84%
that she could
not speak anymore.

00:38:27.160 --> 00:38:29.840 align:middle line:90%
She blah, blah, blah, blah.

00:38:29.840 --> 00:38:32.269 align:middle line:90%
I don't know, don't know, blah.

00:38:32.269 --> 00:38:34.060 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That's what
happened to her mind?

00:38:34.060 --> 00:38:35.270 align:middle line:90%
>>LINDAUER: She drooled.

00:38:35.270 --> 00:38:38.520 align:middle line:84%
She would cry at night, and
that was-- and she would weep,

00:38:38.520 --> 00:38:41.890 align:middle line:84%
and we'd hear her
sobbing in the hallways.

00:38:41.890 --> 00:38:47.420 align:middle line:84%
But she lost the ability
to physically read a book,

00:38:47.420 --> 00:38:49.490 align:middle line:90%
to write anything.

00:38:49.490 --> 00:38:52.490 align:middle line:84%
She could not hold
a cup to drink,

00:38:52.490 --> 00:38:54.850 align:middle line:84%
to lift-- the act of
lifting a cup to your mouth.

00:38:54.850 --> 00:38:56.891 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: She didn't have
the motor coordination?

00:38:56.891 --> 00:38:58.580 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: You'd
spill it all over you.

00:38:58.580 --> 00:39:01.780 align:middle line:90%
Motor coordination was gone.

00:39:01.780 --> 00:39:05.780 align:middle line:84%
Many times we saw black
women particularly

00:39:05.780 --> 00:39:11.480 align:middle line:84%
who were middle class,
who had pretensions,

00:39:11.480 --> 00:39:13.410 align:middle line:90%
who were middle class.

00:39:13.410 --> 00:39:16.340 align:middle line:84%
This was not pretentious,
this was a fact.

00:39:16.340 --> 00:39:17.020 align:middle line:90%
These were--

00:39:17.020 --> 00:39:20.370 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But why-- and they
went after the black women more

00:39:20.370 --> 00:39:21.592 align:middle line:90%
than the other inmates?

00:39:21.592 --> 00:39:23.050 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: More
than anybody else,

00:39:23.050 --> 00:39:24.457 align:middle line:90%
they wanted to degrade them.

00:39:24.457 --> 00:39:26.290 align:middle line:84%
It was all about
degradation and punishment.

00:39:26.290 --> 00:39:28.331 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK, now I want
to get into another part

00:39:28.331 --> 00:39:29.430 align:middle line:90%
of the degradation.

00:39:29.430 --> 00:39:32.620 align:middle line:90%
You had a chaplain there.

00:39:32.620 --> 00:39:35.490 align:middle line:90%
Ratzinger just retired.

00:39:35.490 --> 00:39:38.000 align:middle line:84%
I think we kind of know
where this is going.

00:39:38.000 --> 00:39:41.910 align:middle line:84%
What happened with the
chaplains and the inmates?

00:39:41.910 --> 00:39:45.260 align:middle line:84%
And also, what happened
with the psychiatric staff?

00:39:45.260 --> 00:39:49.740 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: Carswell had
a very high rate of rape.

00:39:49.740 --> 00:39:52.200 align:middle line:84%
And you have to
realize as a prisoner,

00:39:52.200 --> 00:39:56.600 align:middle line:84%
if a guard or Catholic
chaplain decides

00:39:56.600 --> 00:39:59.540 align:middle line:84%
they want to do something
to you, if you fight back,

00:39:59.540 --> 00:40:01.120 align:middle line:84%
you get an assault
charge and you

00:40:01.120 --> 00:40:03.750 align:middle line:84%
can add five years
to your sentence.

00:40:03.750 --> 00:40:05.179 align:middle line:90%
You don't have any rights.

00:40:05.179 --> 00:40:06.970 align:middle line:84%
If they want to do
anything to you, if they

00:40:06.970 --> 00:40:08.720 align:middle line:84%
want to stick their
hands down your pants,

00:40:08.720 --> 00:40:11.860 align:middle line:84%
if they want to
sodomized you, you

00:40:11.860 --> 00:40:13.880 align:middle line:84%
don't talk back to
them when they do it.

00:40:13.880 --> 00:40:14.730 align:middle line:90%
You can't.

00:40:14.730 --> 00:40:18.810 align:middle line:84%
If you do, you are get--
that's an assault charge.

00:40:18.810 --> 00:40:19.810 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: And so--

00:40:19.810 --> 00:40:22.080 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: You will get
a federal assault charge

00:40:22.080 --> 00:40:23.920 align:middle line:90%
adding years to your sentence.

00:40:23.920 --> 00:40:26.040 align:middle line:84%
So this, repeatedly,
women at Carswell

00:40:26.040 --> 00:40:28.587 align:middle line:84%
have been raped by
these guards repeatedly.

00:40:28.587 --> 00:40:30.670 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It's mostly the
guards and the chaplain,

00:40:30.670 --> 00:40:32.310 align:middle line:84%
who have-- they had to get
rid of them didn't they?

00:40:32.310 --> 00:40:34.270 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: A gynecologist
was raping women.

00:40:34.270 --> 00:40:36.050 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yes, and
in fact, I remember

00:40:36.050 --> 00:40:38.180 align:middle line:84%
reading in the book where
you said the women were

00:40:38.180 --> 00:40:41.280 align:middle line:84%
terrified to even go to the
doctor or the gynecologist

00:40:41.280 --> 00:40:43.240 align:middle line:84%
or the chaplain, and
they wouldn't go alone.

00:40:43.240 --> 00:40:44.080 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: They
wouldn't go alone.

00:40:44.080 --> 00:40:44.910 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: They
did a buddy system

00:40:44.910 --> 00:40:46.630 align:middle line:84%
because they knew what
would happen to them.

00:40:46.630 --> 00:40:48.588 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: They knew
what was going to happen.

00:40:48.588 --> 00:40:51.070 align:middle line:84%
And guards, I remember
when I was there,

00:40:51.070 --> 00:40:55.400 align:middle line:84%
guards would say to
younger women than myself,

00:40:55.400 --> 00:40:58.600 align:middle line:84%
but attractive
young inmates, you

00:40:58.600 --> 00:41:02.360 align:middle line:84%
know, hey, I could
give you cigarettes

00:41:02.360 --> 00:41:04.430 align:middle line:90%
if you'll trade favors with me.

00:41:04.430 --> 00:41:06.160 align:middle line:90%
You know, I could protect you.

00:41:06.160 --> 00:41:08.740 align:middle line:84%
I could bring you
extra commissary

00:41:08.740 --> 00:41:12.730 align:middle line:90%
if you'll do stuff with me.

00:41:12.730 --> 00:41:18.410 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So meanwhile, you're
being told by, I don't remember

00:41:18.410 --> 00:41:21.250 align:middle line:84%
whether it was Voss or
whether it was Peterson,

00:41:21.250 --> 00:41:24.160 align:middle line:84%
when they were telling
you, we don't care whether

00:41:24.160 --> 00:41:26.470 align:middle line:84%
you're-- basically, we
don't care about the reality

00:41:26.470 --> 00:41:27.060 align:middle line:90%
of your case.

00:41:27.060 --> 00:41:28.090 align:middle line:90%
It's your word against ours.

00:41:28.090 --> 00:41:29.950 align:middle line:84%
We're doctors, who are they
going to believe here, right?

00:41:29.950 --> 00:41:30.580 align:middle line:90%
>>LINDAUER: That's right.

00:41:30.580 --> 00:41:31.920 align:middle line:90%
That is exactly what they said.

00:41:31.920 --> 00:41:35.820 align:middle line:84%
They said that psychiatry
decides what is reality.

00:41:35.820 --> 00:41:38.130 align:middle line:90%
I remember saying, no way.

00:41:38.130 --> 00:41:39.880 align:middle line:90%
External events decide it.

00:41:39.880 --> 00:41:40.710 align:middle line:90%
I have witnesses.

00:41:40.710 --> 00:41:43.540 align:middle line:84%
Over and over and
over again my defense

00:41:43.540 --> 00:41:46.000 align:middle line:84%
was that I have witnesses
who would provide

00:41:46.000 --> 00:41:49.520 align:middle line:84%
independent confirmation of
who I was and what I had done.

00:41:49.520 --> 00:41:51.820 align:middle line:84%
And I said, I demand the
right to call them into court.

00:41:51.820 --> 00:41:52.970 align:middle line:90%
That is the law.

00:41:52.970 --> 00:41:54.960 align:middle line:84%
You are required
to obey the law.

00:41:54.960 --> 00:41:57.240 align:middle line:84%
Now, the problem
was the Patriot Act.

00:41:57.240 --> 00:41:58.990 align:middle line:84%
Because I was detained
on the Patriot Act,

00:41:58.990 --> 00:42:02.094 align:middle line:84%
I did not automatically
have the right to a hearing,

00:42:02.094 --> 00:42:03.510 align:middle line:84%
because under the
Patriot Act, you

00:42:03.510 --> 00:42:07.720 align:middle line:84%
can be-- you can be detained
indefinitely with no trial.

00:42:07.720 --> 00:42:09.360 align:middle line:84%
They don't have to
give you a hearing.

00:42:09.360 --> 00:42:10.310 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: So, what I found--

00:42:10.310 --> 00:42:11.020 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: They don't
even have to give you

00:42:11.020 --> 00:42:12.630 align:middle line:90%
a hearing under the Patriot Act.

00:42:12.630 --> 00:42:15.940 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It is just
almost incomprehensible

00:42:15.940 --> 00:42:16.860 align:middle line:90%
that this can happen.

00:42:16.860 --> 00:42:17.900 align:middle line:90%
>>LINDAUER: Yes, yes.

00:42:17.900 --> 00:42:20.429 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Now, Judge
Mukasey, at what--

00:42:20.429 --> 00:42:21.470 align:middle line:90%
>>LINDAUER: Sorry, sorry.

00:42:21.470 --> 00:42:23.110 align:middle line:90%
Let me just tell you.

00:42:23.110 --> 00:42:29.090 align:middle line:84%
I was, even then, the
first-- I arrived October 3,

00:42:29.090 --> 00:42:33.120 align:middle line:84%
a day that is burned into
my consciousness forever.

00:42:33.120 --> 00:42:37.190 align:middle line:84%
And I was pretty much OK
until right before Christmas.

00:42:37.190 --> 00:42:39.580 align:middle line:84%
And right before
Christmas, I was

00:42:39.580 --> 00:42:43.064 align:middle line:84%
summoned to an internal
medication hearing.

00:42:43.064 --> 00:42:44.980 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yes, that's
what I wanted to get to.

00:42:44.980 --> 00:42:46.920 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: And that's
when I discovered

00:42:46.920 --> 00:42:50.820 align:middle line:84%
that the government had--
all the bad things that I

00:42:50.820 --> 00:42:53.760 align:middle line:84%
was seeing happen to
all these other women,

00:42:53.760 --> 00:42:56.824 align:middle line:84%
that they wanted
to do this to me.

00:42:56.824 --> 00:42:58.740 align:middle line:84%
Even though I didn't
suffer from any symptoms.

00:42:58.740 --> 00:43:01.540 align:middle line:84%
I had shown no
problems with guards.

00:43:01.540 --> 00:43:03.044 align:middle line:90%
I was very low key.

00:43:03.044 --> 00:43:04.960 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I read the
comments from the guards.

00:43:04.960 --> 00:43:06.065 align:middle line:90%
You have all the documentation.

00:43:06.065 --> 00:43:07.440 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: The
guards said I was

00:43:07.440 --> 00:43:10.210 align:middle line:84%
cooperative, smiling,
good eye contact.

00:43:10.210 --> 00:43:17.190 align:middle line:84%
No behavioral problems,
good hygiene, not a problem.

00:43:17.190 --> 00:43:18.460 align:middle line:90%
I was there.

00:43:18.460 --> 00:43:21.140 align:middle line:84%
I was like, OK, I'm
obviously locked in prison.

00:43:21.140 --> 00:43:25.330 align:middle line:84%
I have to have a decent
attitude about this.

00:43:25.330 --> 00:43:28.060 align:middle line:84%
I was not going to be a
troublemaker in prison.

00:43:28.060 --> 00:43:32.430 align:middle line:84%
I just did not have-- I
avoided the psych staff.

00:43:32.430 --> 00:43:34.630 align:middle line:90%
I refused to play the game.

00:43:34.630 --> 00:43:37.720 align:middle line:84%
We had something
called team meetings.

00:43:37.720 --> 00:43:41.120 align:middle line:84%
Every inmate has them, every
prisoner in the federal system.

00:43:41.120 --> 00:43:43.100 align:middle line:84%
And once a month,
you go and you have

00:43:43.100 --> 00:43:45.696 align:middle line:84%
like a minute with
all the staff to say,

00:43:45.696 --> 00:43:47.070 align:middle line:84%
you know, what's
going on, do you

00:43:47.070 --> 00:43:49.060 align:middle line:84%
have any concerns,
any questions?

00:43:49.060 --> 00:43:51.330 align:middle line:84%
And I said, I'm a
political prisoner.

00:43:51.330 --> 00:43:54.190 align:middle line:84%
I demand my right to
a trial and hearing.

00:43:54.190 --> 00:43:56.760 align:middle line:84%
You have no right to
be holding me here.

00:43:56.760 --> 00:44:00.630 align:middle line:84%
And I am on record telling
you that I expect--

00:44:00.630 --> 00:44:04.279 align:middle line:84%
that I will never give up
until I get my day in court,

00:44:04.279 --> 00:44:05.820 align:middle line:84%
and you can put that
in your reports.

00:44:05.820 --> 00:44:08.360 align:middle line:90%
I refuse to give up my rights.

00:44:08.360 --> 00:44:10.260 align:middle line:84%
And no matter what
you do, you're

00:44:10.260 --> 00:44:12.680 align:middle line:90%
never going to change my mind.

00:44:12.680 --> 00:44:18.310 align:middle line:84%
And so when I was summoned
to this medication hearing,

00:44:18.310 --> 00:44:23.630 align:middle line:84%
they said they wanted to
dope me with Haldol, Ativan,

00:44:23.630 --> 00:44:25.326 align:middle line:90%
and Prozac.

00:44:25.326 --> 00:44:27.700 align:middle line:84%
And I said, well, that's very
interesting because Haldol,

00:44:27.700 --> 00:44:29.080 align:middle line:90%
that's for delusions.

00:44:29.080 --> 00:44:32.160 align:middle line:84%
I have already proven
that my story is correct.

00:44:32.160 --> 00:44:37.490 align:middle line:84%
You, the head psychiatrist,
has interviewed my witnesses.

00:44:37.490 --> 00:44:40.060 align:middle line:84%
He has confirmed
the 9/11 warnings.

00:44:40.060 --> 00:44:43.700 align:middle line:84%
He's confirmed that I worked
as an asset with Richard Fuisz.

00:44:43.700 --> 00:44:46.600 align:middle line:84%
And I've already met
the burden of proof

00:44:46.600 --> 00:44:51.410 align:middle line:84%
that I need to make at this
stage, and I have no intention,

00:44:51.410 --> 00:44:52.610 align:middle line:90%
I will fight you.

00:44:52.610 --> 00:44:56.200 align:middle line:84%
And then I said, Prozac,
that's an extraordinary drug

00:44:56.200 --> 00:45:00.090 align:middle line:84%
to give somebody who
suffers no depression.

00:45:00.090 --> 00:45:03.240 align:middle line:84%
I said, never in my life
have I suffered depression.

00:45:03.240 --> 00:45:06.480 align:middle line:84%
I am a very active,
motivated person.

00:45:06.480 --> 00:45:10.150 align:middle line:84%
And then I said Ativan
for stress, I said,

00:45:10.150 --> 00:45:12.940 align:middle line:84%
outside of prison I
don't suffer stress,

00:45:12.940 --> 00:45:15.360 align:middle line:84%
so I have no
intention of taking--

00:45:15.360 --> 00:45:18.340 align:middle line:84%
the only reason I suffer
from stress in prison

00:45:18.340 --> 00:45:24.710 align:middle line:84%
is because you've detained me
without due process of law.

00:45:24.710 --> 00:45:25.960 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I understand.

00:45:25.960 --> 00:45:29.270 align:middle line:84%
As I was reading your book,
at each turn of events--

00:45:29.270 --> 00:45:31.384 align:middle line:84%
each horrible turn
of events, of course,

00:45:31.384 --> 00:45:33.550 align:middle line:84%
you put yourself in the
person's shoes thinking god,

00:45:33.550 --> 00:45:36.470 align:middle line:84%
how would I-- I would have
been so much worse than you.

00:45:36.470 --> 00:45:39.250 align:middle line:84%
I would not have been
able to keep my cool.

00:45:39.250 --> 00:45:43.020 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: I was
terrified out of my mind.

00:45:43.020 --> 00:45:43.770 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: So you--

00:45:43.770 --> 00:45:45.225 align:middle line:90%
>>LINDAUER: I so scared.

00:45:45.225 --> 00:45:48.110 align:middle line:90%


00:45:48.110 --> 00:45:53.940 align:middle line:84%
I was like my stress
level, my anxiety level--

00:45:53.940 --> 00:45:56.650 align:middle line:84%
again, when you're
first in prison,

00:45:56.650 --> 00:45:58.160 align:middle line:90%
that in itself is a shock.

00:45:58.160 --> 00:46:02.010 align:middle line:84%
I'd never been in prison in my
life, and never expected to.

00:46:02.010 --> 00:46:03.760 align:middle line:90%
I was the good guys.

00:46:03.760 --> 00:46:05.710 align:middle line:84%
We were the ones who
opposed violence.

00:46:05.710 --> 00:46:08.910 align:middle line:84%
We're the ones who are
stopping terrorism.

00:46:08.910 --> 00:46:14.030 align:middle line:84%
I had built up a
long reputation.

00:46:14.030 --> 00:46:15.910 align:middle line:90%
I had an extensive background.

00:46:15.910 --> 00:46:17.740 align:middle line:90%
Well, we call the bona fides.

00:46:17.740 --> 00:46:22.810 align:middle line:84%
And I had tremendous-- I had
the best in the industry.

00:46:22.810 --> 00:46:24.450 align:middle line:84%
Nobody had done
the thing-- that's

00:46:24.450 --> 00:46:26.450 align:middle line:84%
the other thing you don't
really understand even

00:46:26.450 --> 00:46:30.330 align:middle line:84%
listening to all this,
nobody had my bona fides.

00:46:30.330 --> 00:46:33.526 align:middle line:84%
Nobody working in
anti-terrorism.

00:46:33.526 --> 00:46:34.900 align:middle line:84%
You know, these
people, they were

00:46:34.900 --> 00:46:36.694 align:middle line:84%
running around
pretending to be me.

00:46:36.694 --> 00:46:37.360 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:46:37.360 --> 00:46:38.994 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: But I
dealt with Hezbollah.

00:46:38.994 --> 00:46:39.660 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:46:39.660 --> 00:46:42.170 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: I dealt
with Saddam Hussein.

00:46:42.170 --> 00:46:44.090 align:middle line:90%
I dealt with Qaddafi.

00:46:44.090 --> 00:46:47.490 align:middle line:84%
I dealt with the first Osama
bin Laden investigation.

00:46:47.490 --> 00:46:50.270 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So you-- the point is,
you knew what you were doing.

00:46:50.270 --> 00:46:51.280 align:middle line:90%
You're the real deal.

00:46:51.280 --> 00:46:53.910 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: I'm the real deal,
and these other people are just

00:46:53.910 --> 00:46:55.370 align:middle line:90%
fakes and posers.

00:46:55.370 --> 00:46:57.304 align:middle line:90%
And so you're going to judge me?

00:46:57.304 --> 00:46:59.470 align:middle line:84%
You're going to tell me
that I didn't do a good job?

00:46:59.470 --> 00:47:01.520 align:middle line:90%
I can dance circles around you.

00:47:01.520 --> 00:47:04.410 align:middle line:84%
And it's like I'm like
an Olympic performer

00:47:04.410 --> 00:47:06.540 align:middle line:84%
and you're giving
me a nine or a 10.

00:47:06.540 --> 00:47:10.344 align:middle line:84%
And I'm not like some
little high school gymnast.

00:47:10.344 --> 00:47:11.010 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:47:11.010 --> 00:47:11.975 align:middle line:90%
>>LINDAUER: No, huh-uh.

00:47:11.975 --> 00:47:13.100 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: So you knew that.

00:47:13.100 --> 00:47:15.475 align:middle line:84%
You had the advantage of that
experience, that knowledge,

00:47:15.475 --> 00:47:17.940 align:middle line:84%
making it doubly insulting that
you were in this situation,

00:47:17.940 --> 00:47:21.080 align:middle line:84%
but how did you manage to
fight off being drugged?

00:47:21.080 --> 00:47:23.190 align:middle line:90%
I mean, they kept coming at you.

00:47:23.190 --> 00:47:25.090 align:middle line:84%
Well, they came at you
for what, five years?

00:47:25.090 --> 00:47:27.010 align:middle line:84%
Back, and back, and
back, trying to drug

00:47:27.010 --> 00:47:31.110 align:middle line:90%
you to erase that delusion.

00:47:31.110 --> 00:47:34.280 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: Ordinarily when--
the really scary part of it

00:47:34.280 --> 00:47:40.390 align:middle line:84%
was that the prison knew that
ordinarily they would win.

00:47:40.390 --> 00:47:43.070 align:middle line:84%
I had seen other
women who didn't

00:47:43.070 --> 00:47:45.130 align:middle line:84%
want to be drugged
either, and I could

00:47:45.130 --> 00:47:46.800 align:middle line:84%
see the consequences
of what they

00:47:46.800 --> 00:47:49.520 align:middle line:84%
suffered every day
of their lives.

00:47:49.520 --> 00:47:50.710 align:middle line:90%
This is torture.

00:47:50.710 --> 00:47:53.530 align:middle line:84%
This is worse than
water boarding.

00:47:53.530 --> 00:47:55.500 align:middle line:90%
I mean, that's not even a joke.

00:47:55.500 --> 00:48:01.110 align:middle line:84%
These people are-- these
are non-violent offenders.

00:48:01.110 --> 00:48:02.820 align:middle line:84%
Now, if they had been
violent offenders,

00:48:02.820 --> 00:48:04.660 align:middle line:84%
if they were like
attacking the guards

00:48:04.660 --> 00:48:07.920 align:middle line:84%
or attacking other inmates,
you could make an argument.

00:48:07.920 --> 00:48:11.460 align:middle line:84%
But these were women
who were very passive,

00:48:11.460 --> 00:48:14.370 align:middle line:84%
who were traditionally
in their own lives

00:48:14.370 --> 00:48:16.030 align:middle line:90%
very, very, very passive.

00:48:16.030 --> 00:48:17.080 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So if they're
on this drug cocktail--

00:48:17.080 --> 00:48:18.930 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: -letting their
boyfriends run their lives.

00:48:18.930 --> 00:48:19.540 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:48:19.540 --> 00:48:21.060 align:middle line:84%
And now if they're on
this drug cocktail,

00:48:21.060 --> 00:48:22.780 align:middle line:84%
basically, they're
totally incapacitated

00:48:22.780 --> 00:48:23.989 align:middle line:90%
and they sleep all day.

00:48:23.989 --> 00:48:26.030 align:middle line:84%
The system doesn't have
to deal with them at all.

00:48:26.030 --> 00:48:27.947 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: They slept
20 hours a day or more.

00:48:27.947 --> 00:48:30.113 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And they can't--
they can feed themselves.

00:48:30.113 --> 00:48:31.450 align:middle line:90%
They can't bathe themselves.

00:48:31.450 --> 00:48:32.470 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: They
had to be washed--

00:48:32.470 --> 00:48:33.360 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: They're not a
problem to the system.

00:48:33.360 --> 00:48:34.870 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: They
had to wash them--

00:48:34.870 --> 00:48:37.920 align:middle line:84%
they had to be taken by
guards or other inmates

00:48:37.920 --> 00:48:41.130 align:middle line:84%
to the showers, stripped
naked and washed.

00:48:41.130 --> 00:48:43.090 align:middle line:84%
They could not wash
their own hair.

00:48:43.090 --> 00:48:48.630 align:middle line:84%
I had one friend who grieves
me to this day named Courtney,

00:48:48.630 --> 00:48:52.685 align:middle line:84%
and she was so proud
that she took a chair

00:48:52.685 --> 00:48:56.840 align:middle line:84%
and she kept it-- she could
no longer carry the chair,

00:48:56.840 --> 00:48:59.950 align:middle line:84%
but she kept a chair
in the shower rooms

00:48:59.950 --> 00:49:01.560 align:middle line:90%
so that she could just move it.

00:49:01.560 --> 00:49:05.240 align:middle line:84%
And it was hard for her to move
it from one stall to another.

00:49:05.240 --> 00:49:06.830 align:middle line:84%
She couldn't even
do that anymore.

00:49:06.830 --> 00:49:08.550 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But didn't you
guys help each other out?

00:49:08.550 --> 00:49:09.970 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: We did, we
helped each other out.

00:49:09.970 --> 00:49:11.720 align:middle line:84%
But nobody would move
the chair because it

00:49:11.720 --> 00:49:14.970 align:middle line:84%
was like, she had made a
commitment to us that she

00:49:14.970 --> 00:49:16.220 align:middle line:90%
would bathe herself every day.

00:49:16.220 --> 00:49:17.886 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: No matter
how drugged she was.

00:49:17.886 --> 00:49:19.970 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: No matter how
badly she was drugged.

00:49:19.970 --> 00:49:21.950 align:middle line:90%
And she could no longer speak.

00:49:21.950 --> 00:49:23.660 align:middle line:90%
She could no longer write.

00:49:23.660 --> 00:49:27.280 align:middle line:84%
She could no longer
communicate at all.

00:49:27.280 --> 00:49:28.790 align:middle line:90%
Nothing.

00:49:28.790 --> 00:49:31.649 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So we're getting a
picture, not a pretty picture,

00:49:31.649 --> 00:49:32.940 align:middle line:90%
of what it's like inside there.

00:49:32.940 --> 00:49:33.690 align:middle line:90%
>>LINDAUER: Very terrifying.

00:49:33.690 --> 00:49:33.820 align:middle line:90%
Very terrifying.

00:49:33.820 --> 00:49:35.278 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Now, you
have to go back.

00:49:35.278 --> 00:49:38.690 align:middle line:84%
You ultimately have
to go-- you were

00:49:38.690 --> 00:49:41.110 align:middle line:84%
ultimately released,
but only 7 months later.

00:49:41.110 --> 00:49:41.310 align:middle line:90%
>>LINDAUER: Well, hold on.

00:49:41.310 --> 00:49:43.140 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: We've got about
10 minutes left in the show,

00:49:43.140 --> 00:49:43.990 align:middle line:90%
so let's go into it.

00:49:43.990 --> 00:49:46.200 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: OK, I was
locked up for a year.

00:49:46.200 --> 00:49:51.800 align:middle line:84%
And when I refused to
be voluntarily drugged,

00:49:51.800 --> 00:49:56.320 align:middle line:84%
I demanded a hearing
and they held me

00:49:56.320 --> 00:49:58.410 align:middle line:84%
for several-- they
ended up holding me

00:49:58.410 --> 00:50:01.740 align:middle line:84%
at Carswell for seven
months, and then moving me

00:50:01.740 --> 00:50:04.130 align:middle line:84%
to the Metropolitan
Correctional Center

00:50:04.130 --> 00:50:09.440 align:middle line:84%
in Manhattan, which
was considered a worse

00:50:09.440 --> 00:50:14.820 align:middle line:84%
prison because you were on
lockdown 18 hours a day,

00:50:14.820 --> 00:50:16.770 align:middle line:90%
18 to 20 hours a day.

00:50:16.770 --> 00:50:19.890 align:middle line:84%
Which meant that the rest of
the time I was stuck on the top

00:50:19.890 --> 00:50:24.930 align:middle line:84%
bunk not able to go
outside, not able to have

00:50:24.930 --> 00:50:26.930 align:middle line:90%
any physical exercise.

00:50:26.930 --> 00:50:28.640 align:middle line:90%
The food was terrible.

00:50:28.640 --> 00:50:31.440 align:middle line:84%
It was considered one of the
worst prisons in the system,

00:50:31.440 --> 00:50:32.920 align:middle line:90%
to be perfectly honest with you.

00:50:32.920 --> 00:50:35.210 align:middle line:90%
MCC is considered dreadful.

00:50:35.210 --> 00:50:38.820 align:middle line:84%
And yet, I was so relieved
to be out of Carswell

00:50:38.820 --> 00:50:41.992 align:middle line:84%
that I wrote the judge begging
the judge not to send me back.

00:50:41.992 --> 00:50:43.450 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, I
mean, I think you

00:50:43.450 --> 00:50:45.720 align:middle line:84%
felt it was forward
progress of some kind.

00:50:45.720 --> 00:50:47.905 align:middle line:84%
At least you were getting
closer to the sight

00:50:47.905 --> 00:50:49.230 align:middle line:90%
of where you could go to court.

00:50:49.230 --> 00:50:50.360 align:middle line:90%
>>LINDAUER: Absolutely.

00:50:50.360 --> 00:50:55.470 align:middle line:84%
And my beloved companion,
this is what saved to me.

00:50:55.470 --> 00:50:57.950 align:middle line:84%
My beloved companion
JB Fields, who

00:50:57.950 --> 00:51:03.120 align:middle line:84%
died before my case ever ended,
but he was so terrified of what

00:51:03.120 --> 00:51:08.450 align:middle line:84%
was happening he took
my case to the blogs.

00:51:08.450 --> 00:51:10.470 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That was one
of the first big cases

00:51:10.470 --> 00:51:13.740 align:middle line:84%
in what we know now as the
blogosphere, was your case.

00:51:13.740 --> 00:51:15.120 align:middle line:90%
>>LINDAUER: Was my case.

00:51:15.120 --> 00:51:17.930 align:middle line:84%
And until that point,
the corporate media

00:51:17.930 --> 00:51:20.840 align:middle line:84%
had decided what was
important for our society.

00:51:20.840 --> 00:51:23.520 align:middle line:84%
And now the internet
media was just

00:51:23.520 --> 00:51:26.870 align:middle line:84%
beginning-- this was in
2006, and so a lot has

00:51:26.870 --> 00:51:28.270 align:middle line:84%
happened in the
past seven years.

00:51:28.270 --> 00:51:30.780 align:middle line:90%
We forget how far we've come.

00:51:30.780 --> 00:51:32.644 align:middle line:84%
But the internet
was just beginning

00:51:32.644 --> 00:51:33.560 align:middle line:90%
to discover its power.

00:51:33.560 --> 00:51:35.550 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, and also, I
want to just interject something

00:51:35.550 --> 00:51:36.030 align:middle line:90%
here.

00:51:36.030 --> 00:51:37.830 align:middle line:84%
I interviewed a fellow
named Richard Dolan, who's

00:51:37.830 --> 00:51:39.954 align:middle line:84%
written a book about this,
this was included in it.

00:51:39.954 --> 00:51:42.740 align:middle line:84%
And I've heard this from
other situations and sources

00:51:42.740 --> 00:51:46.030 align:middle line:84%
up close that when it
comes to the primary media

00:51:46.030 --> 00:51:48.810 align:middle line:84%
in this country,
CIA is intimately

00:51:48.810 --> 00:51:51.290 align:middle line:84%
involved at either a
publishing or editorial level.

00:51:51.290 --> 00:51:53.560 align:middle line:84%
They will determine if
a story makes it out

00:51:53.560 --> 00:51:55.350 align:middle line:90%
and how it will be presented.

00:51:55.350 --> 00:51:58.250 align:middle line:84%
The New York Times
had your story,

00:51:58.250 --> 00:52:02.140 align:middle line:84%
a junior reporter
had your story down.

00:52:02.140 --> 00:52:04.510 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: Had confirmations
of the 9/11 warnings--

00:52:04.510 --> 00:52:07.030 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: The New York Times
would not let that surface.

00:52:07.030 --> 00:52:09.110 align:middle line:84%
So you end up-- the thing
that really, I mean,

00:52:09.110 --> 00:52:10.240 align:middle line:90%
I had to laugh out loud.

00:52:10.240 --> 00:52:14.100 align:middle line:84%
So you finally do get a
hearing at one point in this,

00:52:14.100 --> 00:52:17.150 align:middle line:84%
and they're saying she's
incompetent to stand trial.

00:52:17.150 --> 00:52:20.190 align:middle line:84%
We have to drug the woman
because of her delusion

00:52:20.190 --> 00:52:23.370 align:middle line:84%
she was a CIA asset and
worked on all these cases.

00:52:23.370 --> 00:52:26.830 align:middle line:84%
And the judge said,
essentially, sirs,

00:52:26.830 --> 00:52:30.050 align:middle line:84%
are you aware of what she
is being accused of and why?

00:52:30.050 --> 00:52:32.490 align:middle line:84%
And it was like, she
is an asset and we're

00:52:32.490 --> 00:52:36.420 align:middle line:84%
saying she's even
a traitorous asset.

00:52:36.420 --> 00:52:38.399 align:middle line:84%
And this whole thing
was absolutely insane.

00:52:38.399 --> 00:52:39.440 align:middle line:90%
>>LINDAUER: That's right.

00:52:39.440 --> 00:52:41.140 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Because that's
all the prosecution had

00:52:41.140 --> 00:52:43.170 align:middle line:84%
was just anything to
shut you up no matter

00:52:43.170 --> 00:52:44.950 align:middle line:90%
how stupid they appeared.

00:52:44.950 --> 00:52:48.370 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: And this is how
crazy the psychiatry industry

00:52:48.370 --> 00:52:51.510 align:middle line:84%
was, and it is a money
making, profit oriented

00:52:51.510 --> 00:52:53.195 align:middle line:90%
business in the courts.

00:52:53.195 --> 00:52:56.540 align:middle line:84%
They actually-- you had the
Justice Department filing

00:52:56.540 --> 00:52:58.470 align:middle line:84%
criminal charges
against me, which

00:52:58.470 --> 00:53:01.570 align:middle line:84%
depended on my relationship
with the diplomats

00:53:01.570 --> 00:53:02.952 align:middle line:90%
at the Iraqi embassy.

00:53:02.952 --> 00:53:04.660 align:middle line:84%
Otherwise, there
couldn't be any charges.

00:53:04.660 --> 00:53:06.076 align:middle line:84%
And then these
crazy psychiatrists

00:53:06.076 --> 00:53:07.885 align:middle line:90%
came in and said that I was--

00:53:07.885 --> 00:53:09.010 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Was making it up.

00:53:09.010 --> 00:53:11.510 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: --inventing
the phony relationships

00:53:11.510 --> 00:53:13.147 align:middle line:90%
with the Iraqi embassy.

00:53:13.147 --> 00:53:14.855 align:middle line:84%
And the judge was
like, do you understand

00:53:14.855 --> 00:53:18.610 align:middle line:84%
that if this didn't occur,
there can't be an indictment?

00:53:18.610 --> 00:53:19.360 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Now, OK.

00:53:19.360 --> 00:53:20.680 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: And the
judge was brilliant.

00:53:20.680 --> 00:53:23.020 align:middle line:84%
And let me just say one
thing about Judge Mukasey

00:53:23.020 --> 00:53:27.260 align:middle line:90%
because he finally saved me.

00:53:27.260 --> 00:53:29.040 align:middle line:90%
He emerged as my hero.

00:53:29.040 --> 00:53:31.080 align:middle line:90%
The blogs were fighting for me.

00:53:31.080 --> 00:53:33.890 align:middle line:84%
That blogs were challenging
it, they were questioning it.

00:53:33.890 --> 00:53:36.820 align:middle line:84%
And Judge Mukasey looked at the
whole thing and he was like,

00:53:36.820 --> 00:53:38.950 align:middle line:90%
this is a disaster.

00:53:38.950 --> 00:53:41.390 align:middle line:84%
We just want to get this
case out of the courtroom.

00:53:41.390 --> 00:53:48.110 align:middle line:84%
Judge Mukasey was a great judge,
a legal straight arrow who

00:53:48.110 --> 00:53:52.280 align:middle line:84%
saw the dangers of the
Patriot Act in his courtroom,

00:53:52.280 --> 00:53:56.150 align:middle line:84%
and he realized that my
case made a lot of bad law.

00:53:56.150 --> 00:54:01.000 align:middle line:84%
And I had a very
weak public defender,

00:54:01.000 --> 00:54:04.820 align:middle line:84%
who was not capable of fighting
for all these other issues.

00:54:04.820 --> 00:54:08.120 align:middle line:84%
And if my case would
have set precedents

00:54:08.120 --> 00:54:11.300 align:middle line:84%
that other cases around the
country would have used.

00:54:11.300 --> 00:54:15.160 align:middle line:84%
And so Judge Mukasey had
a legitimate grievance

00:54:15.160 --> 00:54:16.814 align:middle line:90%
against the Patriot Act itself.

00:54:16.814 --> 00:54:17.480 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:54:17.480 --> 00:54:19.650 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: And he
wanted-- I do believe

00:54:19.650 --> 00:54:22.100 align:middle line:84%
that he wanted to get my
case out of his courtroom

00:54:22.100 --> 00:54:25.140 align:middle line:84%
and to avoid a trial
because he wanted

00:54:25.140 --> 00:54:27.980 align:middle line:84%
to safeguard the
system that he loved.

00:54:27.980 --> 00:54:33.020 align:middle line:84%
And this shows the
horror of my experience

00:54:33.020 --> 00:54:37.710 align:middle line:84%
and the nightmare of how
viciously I was abused.

00:54:37.710 --> 00:54:41.560 align:middle line:84%
And except for the
honesty, the integrity

00:54:41.560 --> 00:54:45.220 align:middle line:84%
of Judge Mukasey-- you know, I
say in my book the old Thomas

00:54:45.220 --> 00:54:49.950 align:middle line:84%
Jefferson quote, "One man of
courage makes a majority."

00:54:49.950 --> 00:54:53.160 align:middle line:84%
And it takes one
person to stand up.

00:54:53.160 --> 00:54:54.920 align:middle line:90%
Never doubt it for a minute.

00:54:54.920 --> 00:54:58.810 align:middle line:84%
It takes one person to stand
up and say this is intolerable.

00:54:58.810 --> 00:55:00.310 align:middle line:84%
We're not going to
put up with this.

00:55:00.310 --> 00:55:02.226 align:middle line:84%
We're not going to let
you get away with this.

00:55:02.226 --> 00:55:06.970 align:middle line:84%
One person can change
everything, and it always does.

00:55:06.970 --> 00:55:10.880 align:middle line:84%
And if you-- and so-- don't--
I hope that you will listen

00:55:10.880 --> 00:55:13.570 align:middle line:84%
to my story and be horrified
of the Patriot Act,

00:55:13.570 --> 00:55:16.260 align:middle line:90%
but don't give up your activism.

00:55:16.260 --> 00:55:18.740 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, and
ultimately, he had to weigh,

00:55:18.740 --> 00:55:20.500 align:middle line:90%
Mukasey had to weigh everything.

00:55:20.500 --> 00:55:22.860 align:middle line:84%
He had to look at what
was going to happen

00:55:22.860 --> 00:55:26.850 align:middle line:84%
if you did stand trial,
which was pretty horrific.

00:55:26.850 --> 00:55:29.810 align:middle line:84%
And what was going to
happen if he just said,

00:55:29.810 --> 00:55:31.105 align:middle line:90%
OK, I'm going with it.

00:55:31.105 --> 00:55:34.440 align:middle line:84%
If she's incompetent then
she can't stand trial,

00:55:34.440 --> 00:55:36.810 align:middle line:90%
and then the epilogue is--

00:55:36.810 --> 00:55:38.800 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: And on
the last day, and so

00:55:38.800 --> 00:55:42.140 align:middle line:84%
it was that on the very
last day of his tenure

00:55:42.140 --> 00:55:45.890 align:middle line:84%
as a federal judge, I was
the very last decision

00:55:45.890 --> 00:55:51.080 align:middle line:84%
of his illustrious career,
and he handed down a blow

00:55:51.080 --> 00:55:55.690 align:middle line:84%
to the prosecution that they
would not be allowed to drug me

00:55:55.690 --> 00:55:56.760 align:middle line:90%
after all.

00:55:56.760 --> 00:55:59.790 align:middle line:90%
And it was a shocker.

00:55:59.790 --> 00:56:04.230 align:middle line:84%
My attorney and me-- I was
convinced that ordinarily they

00:56:04.230 --> 00:56:06.210 align:middle line:84%
would give up and
they'd go along

00:56:06.210 --> 00:56:08.470 align:middle line:84%
with whatever the
prosecution wanted to do.

00:56:08.470 --> 00:56:12.264 align:middle line:84%
And he stood up
for me, and again--

00:56:12.264 --> 00:56:13.930 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: He wouldn't
let them drug you.

00:56:13.930 --> 00:56:15.280 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: So that's
how we avoided it.

00:56:15.280 --> 00:56:16.988 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: To avoid
it, but to get it over

00:56:16.988 --> 00:56:18.610 align:middle line:84%
with it was like you
have to-- you had

00:56:18.610 --> 00:56:22.460 align:middle line:84%
to accept his ruling
of incompetence

00:56:22.460 --> 00:56:25.520 align:middle line:84%
to avoid being drugged, and
also to avoid standing trial,

00:56:25.520 --> 00:56:26.195 align:middle line:90%
and it was over.

00:56:26.195 --> 00:56:28.320 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: It was like
splitting the baby in half.

00:56:28.320 --> 00:56:29.070 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:56:29.070 --> 00:56:31.000 align:middle line:84%
So you had to live with
it, but you were out.

00:56:31.000 --> 00:56:31.790 align:middle line:90%
>>LINDAUER: But I was out.

00:56:31.790 --> 00:56:34.130 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And now we only
have a minute or two left.

00:56:34.130 --> 00:56:35.330 align:middle line:90%
After all of this, Susan--

00:56:35.330 --> 00:56:38.830 align:middle line:84%
>>LINDAUER: I am glad that
I stood up for my values.

